{"id":"1009.4865","submitter":"Ismael Bailleul","authors":"Ismael Bailleul","title":"Probabilistic view on singularities and spacetime boundary","comments":"v2, 15 pages. To appear in J. Math. Phys., Feb. 2011","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.PR math-ph math.MP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The aim of this article is to promote the use of probabilistic methods in the\nstudy of problems in mathematical general relativity. Two new and simple\nsingularity theorems, whose features are different from the classical\nsingularity theorems, are proved using probabilistic methods. Under some energy\nconditions, and without any causal or initial/boundary assumption, simple\nconditions on the energy flow imply probabilistic incompleteness. Also we\nintroduce a probabilistic notion of spacetime boundary which has none of the\npathological defects that the classical boundaries may have.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 24 Sep 2010 15:09:26 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 18 Feb 2011 11:10:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-02-21"}
